com.itko.lisa.test

Class RandSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.itko.lisa.test.RandSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class RandSet
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class implements a random data set. It will assign a given property to one of the values that is given in the test case document.

    Note that this could, but is NOT, extended from com.itko.lisa.test.DataSet because there is no benefit to server-hosting the data set (as most others are). Therefore, this one is serialized with the rest of the TestCase object.

    Here's an example: 

     <RandomList name="PRODUCTID" >
   <values>P101,P201,P301</values>
 </RandomList>
